## Limitations
This report is based on available data and articles up to October 2023. The rapidly evolving nature of the COVID-19 pandemic and public opinion means that new information could alter these findings. Additionally, the psychological and sociopolitical factors influencing beliefs about COVID-19 are complex and multifaceted, requiring ongoing research for a comprehensive understanding.